    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>JAPAN'S GOVERNMENT DEBT RISES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Bloomberg News</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Japan's government debt reaches record $4.7 trillion, outstripping nation's gross domestic product (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Debt reached a record 493 trillion yen ($4.7 trillion) at the end of March as the government continued public works spending to encourage growth. Debt grew 12.7 percent from March 1999, the Ministry of Finance said. The debt is greater than the nation's gross domestic product, which grew to 482.4 trillion yen.</p>
      </block>
